;s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:13;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WebDevStudios";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:14;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"WebDevStudios.com";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8068";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:411:"This year at WordCamp St. Louis, Brian Messenlehner will be speaking, Sarah Pressler will be volunteering, and Cristina Cannon will be in attendance! WordCamp St. Louis is being held on March, 1st 2014 at the Danforth Campus of Washington University &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/24/wds-at-wordcamp-st-louis-2014/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2878:"<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/st-louis.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-8069" alt="st louis" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/st-louis-1024x180.png" width="640" height="112" /></a>This year at <a href="http://2014.stlouis.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp St. Louis</a>, <a title="Brian Messenlehner" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-messenlehner/">Brian Messenlehner</a> will be speaking, <a title="Sarah Pressler" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/sarah-pressler/">Sarah Pressler</a> will be volunteering, and <a title="Cristina Cannon" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/cristina-cannon/">Cristina Cannon</a> will be in attendance! WordCamp St. Louis is being held on <strong>March, 1st 2014</strong> at the Danforth Campus of <a href="http://wustl.edu">Washington University</a> in the <a href="http://wustl.edu/community/visitors/tour/danforth/laboratory-sciences-building.html">Laboratory Sciences Building.</a> You can find Sarah handing out badges and t-shirts and at the <a href="http://2014.stlouis.wordcamp.org/happiness-bar/">Happiness Bar</a> for beginners, while Cristina will be hanging around filling her brain with awesome WordPress knowledge. As for Brian, you can listen to him speak his knowledge about <span style="text-decoration: underline">WordPress as an Application Framework (Intermediate)</span>. You can find Brian in the <strong>User II track at 4:00 PM CST</strong>.</p>\n<p>A description of Brian&#8217;s talk:</p>\n<blockquote><p>Despite starting out as a blogging platform and currently existing primarily as a content management system, WordPress is powerful enough and flexible enough to run any type of web application including hybrid mobile apps. Whether you’re a novice WordPress user or an experienced web developer you can leverage WordPress in many non-traditional ways. We will go over how to rapidly build scalable and secure applications and how to save time and money doing so. We will also showcase some really cool applications and examples of building things with WordPress while thinking out of the box.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Along with presenting and volunteering, WebDevStudios is <a href="http://2014.stlouis.wordcamp.org/sponsors/">sponsoring</a> WordCamp St. Louis this year! We love supporting the WordPress community, and sponsoring events is one of our favorite ways to show it!</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t get the chance to speaking with Brian, Sarah, or Cristina during WordCamp hours, you can catch all three of them at the After Party that is happening directly after the WordCamp is over. Brian, Sarah, and Cristina are looking forward to reconnecting with those of you they&#8217;ve already had the pleasure of meeting, and are also excited to connect with those of you they haven&#8217;t!</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll see you there!</p>\n<div></div>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/24/wds-at-wordcamp-st-louis-2014/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"WDS Welcomes Stacy Kvernmo!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:63:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/10/wds-welcomes-stacy-kvernmo/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/10/wds-welcomes-stacy-kvernmo/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 10 Feb 2014 14:52:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Twitter";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8052";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:362:"We are very excited to welcome our newest member of the team, Stacy Kvernmo! Stacy comes on board as our newest Front End Designer and today is her first day at WebDev, so wish her well. Stacy has been a &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/10/wds-welcomes-stacy-kvernmo/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2246:"<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/stacy-headshot4.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-8053" alt="stacy-headshot4" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/stacy-headshot4-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a>We are very excited to welcome our newest member of the team, Stacy Kvernmo! Stacy comes on board as our newest Front End Designer and today is her first day at WebDev, so wish her well.</p>\n<p>Stacy has been a WordPress fanatic since 2009 and hasn&#8217;t built a site outside of WordPress since then (with the exception of a Drupal site that she was handed, and then rebuilt it in WordPress!). She has been freelancing full-time since 2009, is an active member of the Aurora WordPress Meetup Group and attends WordCamps every chance she gets.</p>\n<p>Stacy&#8217;s web design career began in 2002 at a small creative agency which focused on web design and video production. She was originally hired as a print designer, but they needed more help in web, so she began to do both. At the agency, Stacy was in charge of many aspects of designing a website including creating the initial concept, carrying it out in a visual design, converting PSDs to html/css and building out a full html website (at the time when her company didn&#8217;t use a CMS). As her skills began to develop, she found herself wanting to learn more. Stacy believes she is a kick ass designer. As she has grown in her profession she has realized she REALLY enjoys the actual development of the site and thinks the problem solving aspect is a fun challenge. She has worked hard to become an expert in both visual design and front-end development. By working in small agencies and then doing freelance, she found that you are forced to wear many hats and uses these skills to make great sites for her clients.</p>\n<p>When Stacy isn&#8217;t designing and creating sites in WordPress, she enjoys spending time with her beautiful family ( you can learn more about them on her web site at: <a href="http://www.kverica.com/">http://www.kverica.com/</a>) and doing yoga. You can also follow Stacy on Twitter &#8212; <a href="https://twitter.com/funstacy">@funstacy</a>.</p>\n<p>Welcome to the team, Stacy!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/10/wds-welcomes-stacy-kvernmo/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:51:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"WDS Welcomes Sarah Pressler!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/03/wds-welcomes-sarah-pressler/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/03/wds-welcomes-sarah-pressler/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 03 Feb 2014 16:23:27 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Twitter";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8032";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:439:"WebDevStudios welcomes Sarah Pressler to the team! She&#8217;s joining the team as our newest Technical Project Manager. Her job will focus on bridging the gap between clients and our developers/designers to ensure complete satisfaction with projects. Sarah and WordPress started &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/03/wds-welcomes-sarah-pressler/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2066:"<p>WebDevStudios welcomes Sarah Pressler to the team! She&#8217;s joining the team as our newest Technical Project Manager. Her job will focus on bridging the gap between clients and our developers/designers to ensure complete satisfaction with projects.</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/sarah.png"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-8036" alt="sarah" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/sarah-300x215.png" width="300" height="215" /></a>Sarah and WordPress started a personal relationship in 2004 with v 1.2 (Mingus), and a professional relationship in 2010 with v 2.9 (McRae). She made the switch to full-time WordPress based employment in 2012 with v 3.4 (Green). Like most in the community, what started as a personal hobby has become a career that she loves. As WordPress has grown and matured over the years so has their relationship. From &#8220;Mommy Blogger&#8221; to Technical Project Manager, WordPress has been a central theme. As a mom of four, ranging from ten &#8211; sixteen, project management comes naturally. With training as a classical ballerina and an education in technical writing, the details and execution of well structured project solutions is near and dear to her heart. Client advocacy and customer support have been part of her work ethic since the high school days checking groceries at the hometown store.</p>\n<p>When off the clock and not blowing up Twitter Sarah enjoys life by the lake in Texas. Between school performances and bedtimes she likes to do things that are EXCITING and FUN!! Color Me RAD 5K&#8217;s, Kayaking, old book stores, and hippie little joints in Austin are all places she can be found. Sarah likes to visit new places, never met a road-trip that didn&#8217;t SOUND like a good idea, and never met a stranger. She&#8217;s a lover of fuzzy socks, soft warm blankets straight from the dryer, and micro brewed nutty browns.</p>\n<p>We are proud to welcome Sarah to the team, and excited about the abilities that she will bring to WebDevStudios!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/02/03/wds-welcomes-sarah-pressler/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:60:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"Brian Messenlehner Is Speaking At WordCamp Norway 2014!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/22/brian-messenlehner-is-speaking-at-wordcamp-norway-2014/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/22/brian-messenlehner-is-speaking-at-wordcamp-norway-2014/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 22 Jan 2014 17:45:35 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"Social Network Applications";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"WordCamp";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"WordPress Meetup";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8020";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:397:"Brian is taking a trip across the ocean to speak at WordCamp Norway this year! WordCamp Norway is being held at the Radisson Blu Hotel Nydalen, Oslo. The event will run from the 25th to the 26th of January. You &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/22/brian-messenlehner-is-speaking-at-wordcamp-norway-2014/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2337:"<p>Brian is taking a trip across the ocean to speak at <a href="http://2014.norway.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Norway</a> this year! <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot_on_1.22.2014_at_10.57.00_AM.png"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-8022" alt="Screenshot_on_1.22.2014_at_10.57.00_AM" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot_on_1.22.2014_at_10.57.00_AM.png" width="315" height="204" /></a>WordCamp Norway is being held at the <a title="Radisson Blu Hotel Nydalen, Oslo" href="http://www.radissonblu.no/hotellnydalen-oslo" target="_blank">Radisson Blu Hotel Nydalen, Oslo</a>. The event will run from the 25th to the 26th of January. You can view the entire schedule of WordCamp Norway on their <a href="http://2014.norway.wordcamp.org/schedule/">website</a>.</p>\n<p>Brian is speaking at <strong>15:20 CET on Saturday, January 25th in Room 1</strong>. He will be teaching you all about <span style="text-decoration: underline">Building Web Apps with WordPress. </span></p>\n<p><strong>Description:</strong></p>\n<p><em>WordPress started out as a blogging platform, but throughout the past 10 years, it has become so much more. It doesn&#8217;t matter if you&#8217;re new to the WordPress world, or if you have years of experience under your belt; with WordPress, you can make the impossible, possible. Brian will go through how to build and secure applications at a rapid pace, along with tips on how to save time and money while doing so. You will also get the opportunity to see some awesome apps and examples of things you can do with WordPress while drawing outside of the lines.</em></p>\n<p><em>Brian will also be speaking about <a href="http://apppresser.com/">AppPresser</a> &#8212; The first plugin framework that allows you to create native apps for iOS and/or Android using WordPress. He will illustrate how using AppPresser to create apps is just as easy as creating and customizing a WordPress website.</em></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t get the opportunity to speak with Brian during WordCamp hours, you can catch him at the after party which is being held at the venue itself in the Radisson hotel bar. As always, Brian is excited to reconnect with those of you he&#8217;s already met, and to connect for the first time with those of you he hasn&#8217;t!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/22/brian-messenlehner-is-speaking-at-wordcamp-norway-2014/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"3";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:57:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"WDS at WordCamp Phoenix 2014";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/15/wds-at-wordcamp-phoenix-2014/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/15/wds-at-wordcamp-phoenix-2014/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 15 Jan 2014 15:10:35 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Community Projects";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"WordCamp";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"WordPress Meetup";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8010";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:427:"This year for WordCamp Phoenix, Brad Williams, Lisa Sabin-Wilson, Brian Messenlehner, and Brad Parbs of WDS will be attending and speaking. WebDevStudios is also sponsoring this event! WCPHX is being held January 17-19, 2014 in Chandler, Arizona. Brad Parbs will be &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/15/wds-at-wordcamp-phoenix-2014/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3390:"<p>This year for <a href="http://2014.phoenix.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Phoenix,</a> <a title="Brad Williams" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams</a>, <a title="Lisa Sabin-Wilson" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/">Lisa Sabin-Wilson</a>, <a title="Brian Messenlehner" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-messenlehner/">Brian Messenlehner</a>, and <a title="Brad Parbs" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-parbs/">Brad Parbs</a> of WDS will be attending and speaking. WebDevStudios is also sponsoring this event! WCPHX is being held January 17-19, 2014 in Chandler, Arizona.</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot_on_1.14.2014_at_10.50.48_AM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8012" alt="Screenshot_on_1.14.2014_at_10.50.48_AM" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot_on_1.14.2014_at_10.50.48_AM.png" width="946" height="246" /></a></p>\n<p><a title="Brad Parbs" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-parbs/">Brad Parbs</a> will be speaking on <strong>Friday January 17th, at 9AM in the Advanced Dev Track</strong>. His presentation will tell you all about <span style="text-decoration: underline">Writing Extensible Plugins.</span></p>\n<p>Description:</p>\n<blockquote><p>Functionality in a WordPress site usually requires a variety of plugins, all that need to work together. Sometimes, plugins need to be extended and modified. We’ll go through how to build a plugin that supports extensibility and modification, without hacks. This will be an interactive session, where everyone can share their tips and tricks for this.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a title="Brad Williams" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams</a> will be speaking at <strong>3:15PM Saturday January 18th in the Extension &amp; Development track. </strong>He will be telling you all about <span style="text-decoration: underline">Writing Secure WordPress Code</span>.</p>\n<p>Description:</p>\n<blockquote><p>You’ll learn the proper way to write the most secure code in WordPress. Whether you’re a plugin developer or build themes, it’s extremely important to understand how to secure your code from hacks and exploits. Overlooking some very easy to follow techniques can expose your website to the hackers everywhere. WordPress features a number of built-in methods to help make sure your code is safe and secure, and we’ll cover each and every one in detail.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Brian and Lisa will not be speaking at this event, but will be in attendance in the crowd. If you see any of them, make sure stop and say hi!</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t get the chance to speak with Brad, Brian, Lisa, or Brad P. during WordCamp hours, you can catch them all at the after events including &#8212; <a href="http://2014.phoenix.wordcamp.org/session/wine-and-design-happy-hour-awards/">Wine and Design Happy Hour &amp; Awards</a>, <a href="http://2014.phoenix.wordcamp.org/session/speakers-organizers-and-sponsors-dinner/">Speakers, Organizers, and Sponsors Dinner</a>, and the <a href="http://2014.phoenix.wordcamp.org/session/afterparty-at-chandler-city-hall/">After Party at Chandler City Hall</a>! They all look forward to seeing everyone they&#8217;ve already met and getting to meet new people who have the same passion for WordPress as they do.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/15/wds-at-wordcamp-phoenix-2014/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/