(195, 1, '2014-03-27 21:40:00', '2014-03-27 21:40:00', 'Welcome to New District.\r\n\r\nWe travel across British Columbia seeking great wineries, who emphasize quality in everything they do. We visit vineyards, meet the talented people behind them, learn their stories, and bring it all to you. And best of all, we give you direct access to their wine, right to you door.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://eepurl.com/Q8pj9"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Sign up</span></a> for updates to our wine selection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'From The Editor', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-27 21:40:00', '2014-03-27 21:40:00', '', 4, 'http://192.168.1.65/journal-newdistrict/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(196, 1, '2014-03-27 21:40:19', '2014-03-27 21:40:19', 'Welcome to New District.\r\n\r\nWe travel across British Columbia seeking great wineries, who emphasize quality in everything they do. We visit vineyards, meet the talented people behind them, learn their stories, and bring it all to you. And best of all, we give you direct access to their wine, right to you door.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://eepurl.com/Q8pj9">Sign up</a> for updates to our wine selection.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'From The Editor', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-27 21:40:19', '2014-03-27 21:40:19', '', 4, 'http://192.168.1.65/journal-newdistrict/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(197, 1, '2014-03-28 22:39:30', '2014-03-28 22:39:30', '<h3>A post-prohibition era</h3>\r\nBC’s wine industry was virtually nonexistent prior to BC’s flirtation with prohibition in the early 20s. Its start was with the Growers Wine Company (est. 1927)—yes, the well-known cider-maker today—that initially produced fruit wine. The first grape wine-maker was established several years later in the Okanagan Valley in 1932. However, it was not until the “cottage winery” guidelines of 1978, that BC saw the rise of its small, boutique wineries.\r\n\r\nBC wine has been greatly influenced by government action and regulation. While the 50 years of strict regulation proceeding prohibition largely kept the industry idle, the decades that ensued helped shape the wine you can find in the bottle today. Following the 1988 US Free Trade Agreement, the government provided large-scale funding for growers to pull out the labrusca varieties to be replaced by vinifera plantings, drastically shifting the focus to high-quality wine production. This was followed in 1991 by the establishment of the BC Wine Institute, which runs administers the BC VQA standards. Much more recently, bill C-311 in 2012 eliminated the federal restrictions on transporting wine between provinces for personal enjoyment. Looking at the colourful history of liquor laws in BC, it is clear that government has had a bigger impact on BC’s wine industry than nearly any other wine region.\r\n\r\nWhich brings us to today. BC has over 200 wineries, with many crafting unique wines and emphasizing quality over everything else. The government still plays a significant role: government liquor stores carry a limited selection of high-volume wines that leave the great majority of great, boutique products unexplored and undiscovered by British Columbians.\r\n<h3>Enter New District</h3>\r\nAbout 6 months ago, we set out on a mission to bring you the great wines of British Columbia. After months of deliberation and building, we went out to find some of BC’s most unique wineries. We wanted to bring you great wine that you would have a hard time finding at your local restaurant or liquor store.\r\n\r\nNow, you can discover and purchase BC wine; from our ever-growing list of wineries, right to your door!', 'The Spirited Evolution of BC Wine', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-28 22:39:30', '2014-03-28 22:39:30', '', 9, 'http://192.168.1.65/journal-newdistrict/9-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(198, 1, '2014-03-28 22:39:52', '2014-03-28 22:39:52', 'Welcome to New District.\r\n\r\nWe travel across British Columbia seeking great wineries, who emphasize quality in everything they do. We visit vineyards, meet the talented people behind them, learn their stories, and bring it all to you. And best of all, we give you direct access to their wine, right to you door.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://eepurl.com/Q8pj9">Sign up</a> for updates to our wine selection.', 'From The Editor', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-28 22:39:52', '2014-03-28 22:39:52', '', 4, 'http://192.168.1.65/journal-newdistrict/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
